<h3>Workflow 4: SERP Feature Opportunity Finder</h3>
<p><strong>Goal:</strong> Find keywords where SERP features create ranking shortcuts.</p>
<p><strong>Prompt:</strong>
<em>"Find keywords related to '[your topic]' that trigger featured snippets, People Also Ask boxes, or knowledge panels. Only show keywords with difficulty under 35 and volume above 200. Identify the current featured snippet holder for each."</em></p>
<p>Featured snippets represent a shortcut to position zero. This workflow identifies where those opportunities exist and who currently holds them. That data feeds directly into your content strategy for <a href="/blog/get-cited-ai-search/">AI search optimization</a>.</p>
<h3>Workflow 5: Local Keyword Research at Scale</h3>
<p><strong>Goal:</strong> Generate location-specific keyword lists across multiple cities.</p>
<p><strong>Prompt:</strong>
<em>"Generate keyword lists for '[service type]' across these cities: [city 1], [city 2], [city 3], [city 4], [city 5]. For each city, include the top 10 keywords by volume with difficulty scores. Flag any keywords where no strong local competitor ranks in the top 5."</em></p>
<p>Local SEO keyword research normally requires running the same query 5 to 10 times. One query per city. MCP collapses that into a single prompt. The AI returns all locations in one structured table. This pairs well with a <a href="/blog/improve-google-maps-ranking/">local SEO strategy</a> built around location pages.</p>
